==English==
===Etymology===
Japanese [[数独]], multiple isolations

===Noun===
'''sudoku''' (''plural'' '''sudokus''')

#A type of [[puzzle]] in which the solver must complete a [[magic square]], typically having nine rows and nine columns, which has been subdivided into smaller regions (usually each three rows by three columns in a nine-by-nine puzzle) given some of the entries in the square and the additional condition that the numbers appear once only in each of the smaller regions.

